description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an occupational therapist to join our Integrated Children&#39;s Additional Needs service which provides outcome oriented, child and family centred assessment and intervention to pre-school and school age children in Leeds. The post includes working as part of the multi-disciplinary team providing assessment and intervention to children aged 0-19 with developmental delays, complex physical and sensory disabilities and Autistic Spectrum Disorder. You will work with children in clinical and home settings, nurseries, mainstream schools and the Specialist Inclusive Learning Centres. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are the right candidate, you will have a strong desire to support children and families achieve the goals important to them. You will have experience working in the community with a wide range of children&#39;s needs, specialist skills and knowledge in assessment and intervention and detailed theoretical and clinical knowledge of occupation-centred practice. You will be self-motivated, collaborative and willing to participate in designing and delivering new models of care. You will have evidence of continuing professional development and knowledge of the Children and Families Act and experience in conducting audits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essential Skills: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Occupational Therapy degree&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post-graduate training in relevant specialist field&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in clinical field or closely related clinical area (paediatrics, neurology)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of supervising and delegating to other members of staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specialist assessment, planning and evaluation skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of specialist equipment - assessment and provision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Evidence of workload management/able to work under pressure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competent IT/written communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Awareness of relevant evidence/research&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Able to work as part of a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Positive and flexible attitude&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car Driver&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge and experience of safeguarding practices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Desirable Skills: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SLIP or equivalent leadership training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in Community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience managing staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research/audit experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you&#39;re convinced you&#39;re the best person for this job, let us know more about you! Click apply to submit your application.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
